In a speech commemorating the anniversary of a school shooting in Uvalde, Texas, President Biden called for stricter gun control measures. He expressed empathy for the families affected by the tragedy and emphasized the need to take action to prevent future mass shootings. Biden advocated for banning AR-15 firearms and assault weapons, as well as high-capacity magazines. He also called for universal background checks, national red-flag laws, safe storage of firearms, and an end to immunity from liability for gun manufacturers. Biden urged Americans to come together and make their voices heard to bring about change. He shared a personal experience of grief and offered words of comfort to those who have lost loved ones. The President concluded by honoring the victims of the Uvalde shooting and expressing his hope for healing and resilience.